Topics:

        Arrays Intro
        String Methods
		Arrays Utility
		For Each Loop
        Multi-dimensional Array

Data Structure: to use the data efficiently. allows us to store the data in an organized manner

			1. Array
			2. Collection
			3. Map


regular variable:

		DataType  variableName;
		int        age;
		char       gender;
		String     name;
		....

Array:
		DataType[]  variableName;



Arrays Utility class:  Arrays

		presented in "java.util"


		import java.util.Arrays;

String Methods:

	toCharArray(): returns char array
	split(CharSequence): returns String array

	regular variable:

        int  age = 10;
        int score = 75;
        String name = "Java";


    Array: special variable, size is fixed

        Single Dimensional Array:[] , used for containing multiple elements

                int[] scores = {10, 20, 30, 40};


                toString() ==> for single dimensional arrays ONLY

        Multi Dimensional Array: [][] ..., used for containing multiple arrays


            deepToString() ==> for multi-dimensional dimensional arrays ONLY

